(1313,	53,	'who_can_apply',	'Who Can Apply for a UAE Residence Visa?'),
(1314,	53,	'_who_can_apply',	'field_686b5e431a562'),
(1315,	53,	'who_can_apply_description',	'The UAE offers a variety of residence visa options designed to accommodate different needs, lifestyles and ambitions. To be eligible for a UAE residence visa, an individual must meet at least one of the following criteria:'),
(1316,	53,	'_who_can_apply_description',	'field_686b5ecd1a563'),
(1317,	53,	'who_can_apply_list',	'The UAE offers a variety of residence visa options designed to accommodate different needs, lifestyles and ambitions. To be eligible for a UAE residence visa, an individual must meet at least one of the following criteria:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Employment: Individuals employed by a UAE-based company or government entity.</li>\r\n 	<li>Education: Students enrolled in an accredited educational institution in the UAE.</li>\r\n 	<li>Dependents: Family members (spouse, children, parents or domestic workers) sponsored by a UAE resident or citizen.</li>\r\n 	<li>Investment: Individuals who have made a qualifying investment in a UAE-based business or financial venture.</li>\r\n 	<li>Property Ownership: Investors who own qualifying real estate in the UAE.</li>\r\n 	<li>Retirement: Individuals aged 55 and above meeting specific financial criteria and seeking to retire in the UAE.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMeeting any of these criteria makes you eligible to apply for a UAE residence visa, which allows you to reside legally in the country and access various resident benefits.'),
(1318,	53,	'_who_can_apply_list',	'field_686b5ede1a564'),
(1319,	53,	'types_of_uae_residence_visas',	'Types of UAE Residence Visas'),
(1320,	53,	'_types_of_uae_residence_visas',	'field_686b5efd1a565'),
(1321,	53,	'types_visas_title',	'The UAE offers several types of residence visas. Below are some of the most prominent categories and their key requirements:'),
(1322,	53,	'_types_visas_title',	'field_686b5f021a566'),
(1323,	53,	'golden_visa_title',	'UAE 10-Year Golden Visa'),
(1324,	53,	'_golden_visa_title',	'field_686b5f241a567'),
(1325,	53,	'golden_visa_description',	'The Golden Visa offers long-term residency (5 to 10 years) to investors, entrepreneurs, exceptional talents and other distinguished individuals. The categories under this visa include:'),
(1326,	53,	'_golden_visa_description',	'field_686b5f971a568'),
(1327,	53,	'golden_visa_content',	'<strong>A. Investors in Public Investments</strong>\r\nTo qualify, an investor must meet one of the following criteria:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Deposit at least AED 2 million with a UAE-accredited investment fund; or</li>\r\n 	<li>Hold a valid commercial/industrial license and a memorandum of association reflecting capital of at least AED 2 million.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Additional requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A letter from the Federal Tax Authority confirming annual tax payments of at least AED 250,000.</li>\r\n 	<li>Proof that the invested capital is not financed through a loan.</li>\r\n 	<li>Valid health insurance for self and family.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>B. Real Estate Investors</strong>\r\nTo be eligible for a 5-year Golden Visa:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Own one or more properties in the UAE worth at least AED 2 million.</li>\r\n 	<li>The property can be mortgaged, provided it is financed through approved local banks.</li>\r\n        <li>Eligible family members: spouse, unmarried sons and unmarried daughters.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>C. Entrepreneurs</strong>\r\nEntrepreneurs can qualify for a 5-year Golden Visa if they own a start-up or innovation-focused business valued at AED 500,000 or more.\r\nRequirements include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An auditor’s letter confirming the project’s value.</li>\r\n 	<li>Endorsement from a UAE authority confirming the business is technical or future-oriented.</li>\r\n 	<li>Incubator approval from a UAE-accredited incubator.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>D. Humanitarian Pioneers</strong>\r\nA 10-year visa is available to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Long-serving staff (min. 5 years) of international humanitarian organisations.</li>\r\n 	<li>Recognised contributors to public-interest organisations or major donors to humanitarian causes (min. AED 2 million).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>E. Frontline Workers</strong>\r\nHealthcare workers and other essential frontline professionals (e.g., lab technicians, nurses, pharmacists) may be eligible for a 10-year Golden Visa if they meet specific contribution-based criteria.\r\n. Individuals with Exceptional Talent\r\nThis applies to highly accomplished professionals in fields such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Medicine &amp; Science:</strong> Requires endorsement from the Ministry of Health or relevant authority.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Invention:</strong> Ministry of Economy endorsement for patent-based innovations.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Culture &amp; Arts:</strong> Recognition from the local Department of Culture.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Executive Directors:</strong> Must show proof of higher education, five years of experience, AED 50,000+ salary and a valid work contract.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Athletes:</strong> Recommendation from the General Sports Authority.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Engineers &amp; Scientists:</strong> Academic certification and employment in a critical sector.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>F.Individuals with Exceptional Talent</strong>\r\nThis applies to highly accomplished professionals in fields such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Medicine &amp; Science:</strong> Requires endorsement from the Ministry of Health or relevant authority.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Invention:</strong> Ministry of Economy endorsement for patent-based innovations.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Culture &amp; Arts:</strong> Recognition from the local Department of Culture.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Executive Directors:</strong> Must show proof of higher education, five years of experience, AED 50,000+ salary and a valid work contract.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Athletes:</strong> Recommendation from the General Sports Authority.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Engineers &amp; Scientists:</strong> Academic certification and employment in a critical sector.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>G. Skilled Workers</strong>\r\nTo qualify, applicants must:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Hold a valid UAE work contract.</li>\r\n 	<li>Have a role classified as Skill Level 1 or 2 by MOHRE.</li>\r\n 	<li>Hold a bachelor’s degree or higher.</li>\r\n 	<li>Earn a monthly salary of at least AED 30,000.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1328,	53,	'_golden_visa_content',	'field_686b5fb41a569'),
(1329,	53,	'students_visa_title',	'Students'),
(1330,	53,	'_students_visa_title',	'field_686b60071a56a'),
(1331,	53,	'student_visa_description',	'Top-performing students are recognized as future contributors to the UAE\'s knowledge economy and may be granted long-term residency under the Golden Visa program.\r\n'),
(1332,	53,	'_student_visa_description',	'field_686b61481a56b'),
(1333,	53,	'student_visa_content',	'<strong>Validity and Renewal</strong>\r\nGolden Visas are valid for 5 or 10 years, depending on the category, and are automatically renewable if eligibility conditions continue to be met.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>High School Students:</strong> UAE national students with a 95%+ average may receive a 5-year visa (renewable if their university program exceeds five years).</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>University Students:</strong> Enrolled at a Ministry-recognised university with a minimum GPA of 3.5–3.8 (depending on classification) and having graduated within two years.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Foreign University Graduates:</strong> Graduates of the world’s top 100 universities (as per UAE recognition) may obtain a 10-year visa with a minimum GPA of 3.5 and recent graduation.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1334,	53,	'_student_visa_content',	'field_686b616c1a56c'),
(1335,	53,	'green_visa_title',	'UAE Green Visa'),
(1336,	53,	'_green_visa_title',	'field_686b61aa1a56d'),
(1337,	53,	'green_visa_description',	'The UAE Green Visa is a long-term residency option introduced to attract skilled professionals, freelancers, entrepreneurs and investors. Unlike traditional employment visas, the Green Visa allows greater independence by enabling individuals to sponsor themselves and their families without the need for a UAE-based employer.\r\n'),
(1338,	53,	'_green_visa_description',	'field_686b61ad1a56e'),
(1339,	53,	'green_visa_content',	'<strong>Key Benefits:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Long-term residence (valid for 5 years)</li>\r\n 	<li>Self-sponsorship (no employer required)</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to sponsor first-degree relatives</li>\r\n 	<li>Access to UAE’s public healthcare, education and other services</li>\r\n 	<li>Flexibility to work with or establish any UAE-based business</li>\r\n 	<li>Extended grace period of up to 6 months following visa expiry or cancellation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Strategic Purpose:</strong>\r\nThe Green Visa supports the UAE’s broader strategy to diversify its economy, attract global talent and strengthen its position as a hub for innovation, entrepreneurship and sustainability.\r\nEligibility Categories &amp; Requirements:\r\n<strong>A. Freelancers and Self-Employed Individuals</strong>\r\nMust submit:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A freelance or self-employment permit</strong> issued by the Ministry of Human Resources and Emiratisation (MOHRE)</li>\r\n 	<li>Proof of a bachelor’s degree or specialized diploma</li>\r\n 	<li>Evidence of:<ul>\r\n 	<li>Annual income from self-employment of at least AED 360,000 for the previous two years, <em>or</em></li>\r\n 	<li>Financial solvency for the duration of stay</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>B. Skilled Employees</strong>\r\nMust fulfill the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A valid employment contract</li>\r\n 	<li>Job classified under MOHRE’s occupational levels 1, 2 or 3</li>\r\n 	<li>At least a bachelor’s degree or equivalent qualification</li>\r\n 	<li>A minimum monthly salary of AED 15,000</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Visa Validity:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Issued for 5 years</li>\r\n 	<li>Renewable under the same conditions</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1340,	53,	'_green_visa_content',	'field_686b61b11a56f'),
(1341,	53,	'retirement_visa_title',	'UAE Retirement Visa'),
(1342,	53,	'_retirement_visa_title',	'field_686b62011a570'),
(1343,	53,	'retirement_visa_description',	'The UAE Retirement Visa offers long-term residency for retirees aged 55 and above who wish to settle in the country post-retirement. It provides a unique opportunity to enjoy the UAE’s modern infrastructure, high quality of life and world-class healthcare.\r\n'),
(1344,	53,	'_retirement_visa_description',	'field_686b62051a571'),
(1345,	53,	'retirement_visa_content_copy',	'<strong>Eligibility Criteria:</strong>\r\nApplicants must meet one of the following financial criteria:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Minimum of 15 years of work experience</strong>, either in the UAE or abroad, or be <strong>aged 55 years or older</strong> at the time of application</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Own real estate in the UAE</strong> valued at <strong>AED 1 million or more</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Maintain financial savings</strong> of at least <strong>AED 1 million</strong> in a UAE bank</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Have a monthly income</strong> of at least <strong>AED 20,000</strong> (<em>or AED 15,000 for Dubai residents</em>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Required Documentation:</strong>\r\n<strong>General:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Passport copy</strong> (applicant and dependents)</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Current UAE residency visa</strong> (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Emirates ID</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Marriage certificate</strong> (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Real Estate Ownership:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Copy of title deed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Savings-Based:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Proof of retirement</li>\r\n 	<li>Bank-issued letter confirming UAE-based savings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Fixed Income-Based:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Retirement letter</li>\r\n 	<li>Proof of income</li>\r\n 	<li>6-month bank statement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Combination of Property &amp; Savings:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Copy of title deed</li>\r\n 	<li>Savings confirmation letter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Visa Validity:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Issued for 5 years</li>\r\n 	<li>Renewable upon meeting eligibility criteria</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1346,	53,	'_retirement_visa_content_copy',	'field_686b62071a572'),
(1347,	53,	'retirement_visa_content_copy2',	''),
(1348,	53,	'_retirement_visa_content_copy2',	'field_686b62581a575'),
(1349,	53,	'employment_visa_title',	'UAE Employment Visa'),
(1350,	53,	'_employment_visa_title',	'field_686b62531a573'),
(1351,	53,	'employment_visa_description',	'The UAE Employment Visa is the most common residency route for foreign professionals working in the UAE. This visa allows foreign nationals to reside and work legally in the country under the sponsorship of a licensed employer.'),
(1352,	53,	'_employment_visa_description',	'field_686b62551a574'),
(1353,	53,	'employment_visa_content',	'<strong>Sponsorship:</strong>\r\nThe employer acts as the visa sponsor. Eligible sponsors include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Private companies (mainland or free zone)</li>\r\n 	<li>Government-owned or semi-government entities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For Mainland Company Employees:</strong>\r\nCompany Documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Trade License</li>\r\n 	<li>Immigration Establishment Card</li>\r\n 	<li>Labour Card</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Employee Documents:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Passport copy</li>\r\n 	<li>Passport-size photo (white background)</li>\r\n 	<li>Education certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous UAE residency visa (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous Emirates ID (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Tourist visa copy (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Health insurance (DHA-approved)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For Free Zone or Government Entity Employees:</strong>\r\nCompany Documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Online visa application form</li>\r\n 	<li>Trade License</li>\r\n 	<li>Immigration Establishment Card</li>\r\n 	<li>Office Lease Agreement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Employee Documents:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Passport copy</li>\r\n 	<li>Passport-size photo</li>\r\n 	<li>Offer or appointment letter</li>\r\n 	<li>Education certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous residency visa (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous Emirates ID (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Tourist visa copy (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Health insurance (DHA-approved)</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1354,	53,	'_employment_visa_content',	'field_686b62671a576'),
(1355,	53,	'investor_visa_title',	'UAE Investor Visa'),
(1356,	53,	'_investor_visa_title',	'field_686b641c1a577'),
(1357,	53,	'investor_visa_description',	'Entrepreneurs and investors who contribute to the UAE’s economic growth are eligible for long-term residency through the Investor Visa program'),
(1358,	53,	'_investor_visa_description',	'field_686b64201a578'),
(1359,	53,	'investor_visa_content',	'The UAE Investor Visa is available to individuals who either:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Own a business or hold shares in an existing UAE company</li>\r\n  <li>Intend to establish a new business in the UAE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis visa grants the right to live and work in the UAE and is often a gateway to long-term residency through the Golden or Green Visa programs.\r\n<strong>Required Documents:</strong>\r\nFor Mainland Company Investors:\r\nCompany Documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Trade License</li>\r\n 	<li>Immigration Establishment Card</li>\r\n 	<li>Memorandum of Association</li>\r\n 	<li>Local Service Agent Agreement</li>\r\n 	<li>Partnership Agreement (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>List of Company Partners</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Investor Documents:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Passport copy</li>\r\n 	<li>Passport-size photo (white background)</li>\r\n 	<li>Personal bank statement (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous residency visa (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous Emirates ID (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For Free Zone or Government Entity Investors:</strong>\r\nCompany Documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Trade License</li>\r\n 	<li>Share Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Immigration Card</li>\r\n 	<li>Memorandum of Association</li>\r\n 	<li>Certificate of Incorporation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Investor Documents:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Passport copy</li>\r\n 	<li>Passport-size photo</li>\r\n 	<li>Personal bank statement (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous residency visa (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous Emirates ID (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Visa Validity:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Valid for 3 years</li>\r\n 	<li>Renewable, subject to continued ownership or shareholding</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1360,	53,	'_investor_visa_content',	'field_686b64251a579'),
(1361,	53,	'family_visa_title',	'UAE Family Visa'),
(1362,	53,	'_family_visa_title',	'field_686b646b1a57a'),
(1363,	53,	'family_visa_description',	'The UAE Family Visa allows residents, regardless of profession, to sponsor immediate family members, including spouses, children and parents.'),
(1364,	53,	'_family_visa_description',	'field_686b646d1a57b'),
(1365,	53,	'family_visa_content',	'<strong>Eligibility &amp; Sponsorship Criteria:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The sponsor must earn a minimum monthly salary of AED 4,000 or AED 3,000 plus accommodation</li>\r\n 	<li>Both male and female residents can sponsor family members</li>\r\n 	<li>Dependents aged 18 and over must pass a medical fitness test at a UAE-approved health center</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Special Notes:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Mothers may sponsor children in special cases, as approved by the ICP</li>\r\n 	<li>The family visa must be applied for within 60 days of the dependents’ entry on an entry permit</li>\r\n 	<li>Medical fitness is required for visa issuance; those with inactive pulmonary TB may still qualify under conditional certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Parents may be sponsored with a 1-year renewable visa, regardless of the sponsor’s visa duration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Required Documents:</strong>\r\nSponsor Documents:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Passport copy</li>\r\n 	<li>UAE residence visa copy</li>\r\n 	<li>Original Emirates ID</li>\r\n 	<li>Labour card and employment contract (MOHRE or Free Zone)</li>\r\n 	<li>Salary certificate (Free Zone/government employees)</li>\r\n 	<li>Ejari or Tawtheeq certificate (proof of tenancy)</li>\r\n 	<li>Latest utility bill</li>\r\n 	<li>Bank statement (if required)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Dependent Documents:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Passport (valid for at least 6 months)</li>\r\n 	<li>Passport-size photo (white background)</li>\r\n 	<li>Previous UAE visa (if applicable)</li>\r\n 	<li>Marriage certificate (for spouses)</li>\r\n 	<li>Birth certificate (for children)</li>\r\n 	<li>DHA-approved health insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Visa Validity:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Issued for 1 to 2 years, or aligned with the sponsor’s visa validity</li>\r\n 	<li>Automatically cancelled if the sponsor’s visa is cancelled</li>\r\n 	<li>A 30-day grace period is granted for dependents to leave or transfer sponsorship after cancellation; fines may apply after that</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1366,	53,	'_family_visa_content',	'field_686b646f1a57c'),
(1367,	53,	'general_document_title',	'General Document Requirements for a Dubai Residence Visa'),
(1368,	53,	'_general_document_title',	'field_686b64d81a57d'),
(1369,	53,	'general_document_description',	'Whether applying as an employee, investor, retiree, student or dependent, applicants must submit specific documentation to complete the residence visa process in the UAE. The requirements vary depending on visa type, but the following are generally applicable:'),
(1370,	53,	'_general_document_description',	'field_686b64e41a57e'),
(1371,	53,	'general_core_requirements',	'<strong>Core Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Original Passport (valid for at least 6 months)</li>\r\n 	<li>Entry Visa (entry permit issued before arriving or as part of the application process)</li>\r\n 	<li>Sponsor Letter from a university, employer or UAE-based relative, depending on visa category</li>\r\n 	<li>Medical Fitness Test including blood tests, chest X-rays and HIV screening, conducted at an approved UAE health centre</li>\r\n 	<li>Certificate of Good Conduct from your home country’s police authority (varies by visa type)</li>\r\n 	<li>DHA-Approved Health Insurance policy covering the applicant during their stay in the UAE</li>\r\n 	<li>Application for Emirates ID via the Federal Authority for Identity, Citizenship, Customs &amp; Port Security</li>\r\n 	<li>Bank Deposit (required for certain visa categories; amount varies)</li>\r\n 	<li>Birth or Marriage Certificate, where applicable, particularly for family and dependent visas</li>\r\n 	<li>Completed Residence Visa Application Form, including personal details, passport information and supporting documents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMeeting these requirements ensures a streamlined and compliant visa application process, allowing you to establish legal residency and enjoy life in the UAE with confidence.'),
(1372,	53,	'_general_core_requirements',	'field_686ba29b1a57f'),
(1373,	53,	'visa_steps_title',	'How to Apply for a UAE Residence Visa'),
(1374,	53,	'_visa_steps_title',	'field_686ba2ba1a580'),
(1375,	53,	'visa_steps_description',	'Applying for a UAE residence visa involves a clear, step-by-step process. Whether you are relocating for work, study, investment or retirement, following the correct procedure ensures a smooth experience.'),
(1376,	53,	'_visa_steps_description',	'field_686ba2c71a581'),
(1377,	53,	'step1_title',	' Secure a Sponsor'),
(1378,	53,	'_step1_title',	'field_686ba3211a582'),
(1379,	53,	'step1_description',	'To begin the process, you must have a sponsor in the UAE. Depending on your situation, your sponsor may be:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>A UAE-based company (for employment visas)</li>\r\n  <li>A UAE citizen or resident (for family/dependent visas)</li>\r\n  <li>An accredited educational institution (for student visas)</li>\r\n  <li>Yourself (in cases of investor, freelancer or retirement visas under self-sponsorship)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe sponsor is responsible for initiating the visa application and ensuring all requirements are met.'),
(1380,	53,	'_step1_description',	'field_686ba33a1a583'),
(1381,	53,	'step2_title',	'Obtain an Entry Permit'),
(1382,	53,	'_step2_title',	'field_686ba3451a584'),
(1383,	53,	'step2_description',	'The sponsor must apply for an entry permit (also known as an e-visa) through the Federal Authority for Identity, Citizenship, Customs & Port Security (ICP) or the General Directorate of Residency and Foreigners Affairs (GDRFA). Entry permits can also be processed through licensed GDRFA typing centers.'),
(1384,	53,	'_step2_description',	'field_686ba3541a585'),
(1385,	53,	'step3_title',	'Prepare Required Documents'),
(1386,	53,	'_step3_title',	'field_686ba3871a586'),
(1387,	53,	'step3_description',	'Gather all necessary documents for your visa type. These typically include:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>A valid passport</li>\r\n  <li>Passport-sized photo</li>\r\n  <li>Entry permit</li>\r\n  <li>Proof of accommodation or sponsor’s tenancy contract</li>\r\n  <li>Medical test results</li>\r\n  <li>Health insurance</li>\r\n  <li>Additional supporting documents depending on visa category (e.g., employment contract, proof of investment, university admission letter)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(1388,	53,	'_step3_description',	'field_686ba3dc1a58b'),
(1389,	53,	'step4_title',	'Submit Residence Visa Application'),
(1390,	53,	'_step4_title',	'field_686ba3981a587'),
(1391,	53,	'step4_description',	'Your sponsor is responsible for submitting the residence visa application to the GDRFA. In the case of self-sponsorship (for investors, freelancers, retirees), you may complete this step independently or through an authorised service provider.'),
(1392,	53,	'_step4_description',	'field_686ba3ee1a58c'),
(1393,	53,	'step5_title',	'Pay the Visa Fees'),
(1394,	53,	'_step5_title',	'field_686ba3a81a588'),
(1395,	53,	'step5_description',	'Visa fees vary based on the type and duration of the visa. Payments are made at the time of application, and additional fees may apply for medical tests, Emirates ID and service charges.'),
(1396,	53,	'_step5_description',	'field_686ba3fd1a58d'),
(1397,	53,	'step6_title',	'Receive Approval and Visa Stamping'),
(1398,	53,	'_step6_title',	'field_686ba3ba1a589'),
(1399,	53,	'step6_description',	'Once the application is approved, your visa will be stamped in your passport. You are now legally permitted to reside in the UAE.'),
(1400,	53,	'_step6_description',	'field_686ba40c1a58e'),
(1401,	53,	'step7_title',	' Apply for Emirates ID'),
(1402,	53,	'_step7_title',	'field_686ba3ca1a58a'),
(1403,	53,	'step7_description',	'All UAE residents must obtain an Emirates ID, which serves as the official identification card. The Emirates ID is valid for the same duration as your residence visa and is issued by the ICP after biometric data is collected.\r\nVisa Duration\r\nResidence visas are typically valid for:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>1 to 3 years for standard employment or family sponsorship</li>\r\n  <li>5 to 10 years for self-sponsored visas such as the Green or Golden Visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>All visas are renewable subject to meeting the relevant requirements.</p>\r\n'),
(1404,	53,	'_step7_description',	'field_686ba41c1a58f'),
(1405,	53,	'advantages',	'Obtaining a residence visa opens the door to numerous benefits and long-term opportunities in the UAE:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Open a Bank Account</strong><br>\r\n    Gain access to local banking services and financial tools tailored to residents.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Access Credit and Financial Facilities</strong><br>\r\n    Qualify for loans, credit cards and investment services.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Apply for a UAE Driving Licence</strong><br>\r\n    Eligible residents can apply for a local driving licence.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Access Government Healthcare and Insurance</strong><br>\r\n    Benefit from public health services and DHA-approved insurance coverage.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Enrol Children in Schools</strong><br>\r\n    Register your children in government or private educational institutions.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Legally Work and Invest</strong><br>\r\n    Live, work and invest freely across the UAE economy.\r\n  </li>\r\n  <li>\r\n    <strong>Travel Privileges</strong><br>\r\n    Some nationalities may receive visa-free or visa-on-arrival access to select countries when holding a UAE residence visa.\r\n  </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(1406,	53,	'_advantages',	'field_686ba44a1a590'),
(1407,	53,	'help',	'Navigating the UAE residence visa process can be complex - especially for first-time applicants or foreign investors. Our team provides end-to-end support to ensure your visa application is smooth, compliant and stress-free. We assist with:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Identifying the most suitable visa pathway based on your goals</li>\r\n  <li>Preparing and reviewing application documents</li>\r\n  <li>Coordinating medical tests and Emirates ID appointments</li>\r\n  <li>Liaising with government authorities on your behalf</li>\r\n  <li>Providing ongoing support for renewals and family sponsorship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhether you are an individual or a company sponsoring employees, we simplify the process so you can focus on what matters most - starting your new chapter in the UAE with confidence.'),
(1408,	53,	'_help',	'field_686ba45b1a591'),
